#EdTech Textbook Version and Peer Review Analysis

This project demonstrates SQL-based analysis of an EdTech publishing dataset using self joins to answer real-world business questions around textbook edition tracking and author peer review assignments.

The analysis focuses on identifying updated textbook versions and mapping author-to-author review relationships within the publishing workflow.

--

#Objective

The primary goals of this analysis were to:

-Track current textbooks and their out-of-date versions
Identify textbooks that have updated editions
Analyze author peer review assignments
-Strengthen SQL skills using self joins and aliases
-Improve understanding of how one table can relate to itself in multiple ways

#Business Questions

-Which textbooks are current, and which older editions do they replace?
-Which textbooks have updated versions?
-Which authors are currently assigned to review another author’s work?
-How can self joins be used to compare rows within the same table?
-How can textbook version tracking support publishing decisions?
