#SQL Analysis

-1. All Textbooks with Their Previous Versions
SELECT A.Subject,
       A.Title AS textbook,
       B.Title AS previous_version
FROM Textbooks A
LEFT JOIN Textbooks B
    ON A.TextbookID = B.UpdatedVersion
ORDER BY textbook;

Business Insight:
This query provides a full list of textbooks and shows whether each current title replaced an older edition.

Business Impact:
Helps publishing and curriculum teams understand textbook version history and identify where updated editions have replaced prior books.

-2. Textbooks That Have Updated Versions
SELECT A.Subject,
       A.Title AS textbook,
       B.Title AS previous_version
FROM Textbooks A
INNER JOIN Textbooks B
    ON A.TextbookID = B.UpdatedVersion
ORDER BY textbook;

Business Insight:
This query isolates only textbooks that are known updated replacements for older editions.

Business Impact:
Useful for monitoring edition rollouts, supporting sales outreach, and ensuring schools transition to the most current materials.

-3. Authors Reviewing Other Authors
SELECT authors.AuthorID,
       authors.Name AS Reviewer,
       peers.Name AS Being_reviewed
FROM Authors authors
INNER JOIN Authors peers
    ON authors.Reviewing = peers.AuthorID
ORDER BY authors.AuthorID;

Business Insight:
This query maps authors who are assigned to review another author’s work.

Business Impact:
Supports editorial workflow visibility and helps teams understand peer review assignments across the author network.
